  "mixedPack": {
    "_comment": "Per-tile layout choice (SLAB-FORMAT §3): one pack, two tiles, gate 0.5, same axes/partials/measures as above. Tile 0/0/0 (5 grain cells / (2 marks × 6 cells) = 0.417 < gate) → sparse; tile 0/0/1 (4 / (1 × 6) = 0.667 ≥ gate) → dense. Both languages: the C# writer picks each tile's layout from its own occupancy and records only the exception vs the view default (sparse), so tileLayouts = {0/0/1: dense}; the reader/decoder branches per tile; folds are byte-identical to whole-slab folds. Dense planes: null = empty cell (0 additive, NaN min/max); cumulative along quarter within each operator run. Tile 0/0/0 reuses the top-level facts (its sparse encoding and folds are the top-level sparse/folds).",
    "gate": 0.5,
    "viewDefaultLayout": "sparse",
    "tileLayouts": { "0/0/1": "dense" },
    "tiles": [
